data.name: Classic Beef Wellington with Garlic Mashed Potatoes and Asparagus
data.quickTastyDescription: A show-stopping beef tenderloin wrapped in flaky pastry, served with creamy garlic mashed potatoes and fresh asparagus.
detailedCookingInstructions: Sear the beef tenderloin in a hot skillet until browned on all sides, about 2-3 minutes per side. Season with salt and pepper. Allow to cool.
In the same skillet, sauté finely chopped mushrooms until moisture has evaporated, about 10 minutes. Stir in thyme and let cool.

Lay out prosciutto slices on a sheet of plastic wrap, slightly overlapping. Spread the mushroom mixture over the prosciutto, then place the beef on top. Roll tightly using the plastic wrap and refrigerate for 15 minutes.

Roll out puff pastry on a floured surface. Remove the beef from the plastic wrap and place it in the center of the pastry. Wrap the pastry around the beef, sealing the edges. Brush with egg yolk mixed with a splash of water.

Place the wrapped beef on a baking sheet and bake for 25-30 minutes or until the pastry is golden brown and the internal temperature of the beef reaches 130°F (54°C) for medium-rare. Let rest for 10 minutes before slicing.
For the garlic mashed potatoes, peel and chop potatoes. Boil in salted water until tender, about 15-20 minutes. Drain and mash with heavy cream, minced garlic, salt, and pepper until smooth.
For the asparagus, toss with olive oil, salt, and pepper, then roast in the oven for 10-15 minutes until tender and slightly crisp.
